The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNCâs first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1â overall length and an 18.5â cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3â rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".
This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil. The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. I am selling my Savage 110 BA .338 Lapua Magnum. The Savage 110 BA Law Enforcement is a bolt-action long-range tactical rifle chambered in .338 Lapua Mag.
The 110 is part of Savageâs Law Enforcement series and is equipped with the patented AccuStock and AccuTrigger (Accu abbreviated for accuracy). 

The AccuStock uses a fiberglass lining within the stock, which wedges the action in the stock (on top of screwing it in) rendering it immobile ensuring the rifle will shoot straight. The barrel is free-floated, so the stock doesnât interfere with its action. The actual trigger of the 110 requires a very short pull, which is great for a precision rifle, but since it is a tactical rifle light triggers pose a safety hazard because of accidental discharges. So Savage implemented the AccuTrigger, which is basically a trigger on a trigger. The AccuTrigger prevents accidental discharges by using an internal lever that must be lifted before the firing pin can punch forward. Also, shooters donât have to switch the safety off after sighting in.

title: For Sale:  Ithaca Minier Grade 5 extremely rare 12 double
location: New York, New York, United States
postcontent: Gun is not perfect but extremely rare and in very nice condition. The Minier was only produced between 1907 and 1908 and very very few high grade ones were produced and even fewer grade 5's. 30" very fancy and fine star damascus barrels choked Full x Full with shiny unpitted bores, extractors and lots of dark damascus pattern remaining. The exquisitely engraved receiver retains some case color. Action locks up tight and on face with all numbers matching. LOP is 14 1/4" to the original Ithaca hard rubber butt plate. Drop is 1 3/4" and 3". Wood and checkering are very very good. The down side to the gun is the stock is a very well done replacement and the trigger tang does not have any engraving on the pistol grip area. Everything else is very nice. The engraving is stunning. Only high grade Minier I have had.
